The paper deals with visual question answering (VQA) models, which typically fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed neural network component involves object proposals, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as object detection and segmentation, further supporting the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of attention mechanisms, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new component to improve counting accuracy, which falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
